column2: “Appendix  F – Relative Risk Tables”, Society of Actuaries. Accessed: July, 2018 from http://www.soa.org/Files/Zip/research-2008-vbt-report-app-f.pdf
2008 Valuation Basic Table (VBT) Relative Risk (RR) - Female, 100%, Smoker, Age Nearest Birthday. Minimum Age: 18. Maximum Age: 90.

The 2008 VBT is composed of two aggregate or combined standard and preferred risk tables. The aggregate tables are referred to as the Primary Table and the Limited Underwriting Table.  The Team then subdivided the Primary Table into multiple tables to reflect the range of expected mortality from super-preferred to residual standard risk.  These multiple tables are referred to as the Relative Risk (RR) Tables. This RR 100 table and the corresponding Primary table are essentially the same except that ages 0-17 are not included in the RR 100 table. Data Certified: 07/2018.
